FBIS3-38705 "drweu025_j_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-025 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Feb 1994 ITALY & VATICAN CITY Army Officer Killed in 6 Feb Somalia Attack LD0602182594 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1740 GMT 6 Feb 94 LD0602182594 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext Language: Italian Article Type:BFN [Text] An Italian officer, Lieutenant Giulio Ruzzi, 29, was killed today in Somalia. A soldier from the same Italian contingent, Franco Ratenni, 22, was seriously injured. According to information from the Defense Ministry, a column from the Italian contingent, UNOSOM [UN Operation in Somalia] 2, which was on its way from Bulo Burti to Balad carrying food, was attacked by a hail of bullets at 1700. Lieutenant Ruzzi died while being transported to the hospital in Giohar.
